<dl id="n11121a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11121a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11121a"> 121(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> appetites <font color="green">[in art]</font> / hunger?</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Jours difficiles</b> La faim me d&eacute;vorait; j&apos;&eacute;tais <mark>br&ucirc;lant</mark>; le sommeil m&apos;avait fui; je su&ccedil;ais des morceaux de linge que je trempais dans l&apos;eau; je m&acirc;chais de l&apos;herbe et du papier. Quand je passais devant des boutiques de boulangers, mon tourment &eacute;tait horrible. Par une rude soir&eacute;e d&apos;hiver, je restai deux heures plant&eacute; devant un magasin de fruits secs et de viandes fum&eacute;es, avalant des yeux tout ce que je voyais: j&apos;aurais mang&eacute;, non seulement les comestibles, mais leurs boites, paniers et corbeilles. <br><font color="green">[Hard days: Hunger consumed me. I was burning-hot; sleep had deserted me. I sucked bits of linen soaked in water; I chewed grass and paper. When I passed before bakers&apos; shops, the pangs were dreadful. One raw winter evening I stood for two hours in front of a shop that sold dried fruit and smoked meat, devouring with my eyes everything I saw: I could have eaten the victuals together with their boxes, containers and baskets.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 73</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
